<p>A special cleanup case was the old OpenOffice &lt;-&gt; PostgreSQL driver. “That was ‘bitrotten’ as we say. It only worked up to version 3.2 .. So I reworked it: integrated the native LibreOffice &lt;-&gt; PostgreSQL driver into LibreOffice proper, enhanced it, ported it to the latest LibreOffice version. Lots of advantages for PostgreSQL access obviously.”</p>
